HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 254
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Dr. Frank Maxey "Max"
Petett.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Dr. Frank Maxey "Max" Petett; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Petett was an exemplary and conscientious public servant and
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow
citizens; and
WHEREAS, born on June 29, 1965, in Glasgow, Kentucky, to Frank Petett and Francis
Farmer Petett, Dr. Petett graduated from Tompkinsville High School and had earned a Ph.D. in
Educational Leadership, which he used to great effect as the principal of Jackson County High
School; and
WHEREAS, he and his late wife, Tracy Lynn Petett, cherished many tender years
together, many of those hours savored amid the beauty of Dale Hollow Lake, and they always
set aside time to be well spent with their children and grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, thoughtful of this world and the next, Dr. Petett was a faithful member of
Rockbridge Missionary Baptist Church; and
WHEREAS, he was deeply devoted to his family, and he endeavored to remain true to
family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Frank Petett is survived by his children, Parker (Alexis) Petett, Spencer
(Cassie) Petett, Hunter (Tim) Coe, Brooks (Haley) Murphy, and Braden Murphy and his
companion, Landri; his grandchildren, Paxton Crue, Stormy Ann, and Camilla Elizabeth; his
siblings, Lisa (Mike) Davis, Connie (Chris) Anggelis, and Regina (John) Sullivan; his wife's aunt,
Demetria Finley; and several nieces and nephews; and
